title: Harbaugh vs. Harbaugh: Ravens-Chargers clash reignites a lifelong competition
description: For the Baltimore and Los Angeles coaches, the "Monday Night Football" matchup marks their first matchup since Super Bowl XLVII.
author: Jamison Hensley

title: UConn loses to Memphis in OT as rally falls short
description: Unranked Memphis withstands a late rally to take down No. 2 UConn 99-97 in overtime at the Maui Invitational.

title: Littler handed potential Sherrock showdown at World Darts Championship
description: Luke Littler faces a potential showdown against Fallon Sherrock at the Paddy Power World Darts Championship, while Luke Humphries will begin his title defence against Thibault Tricole or Joe Comito.

title: Carra slams Salah's contract comments as 'selfish'
description: Jamie Carragher is "very disappointed" with Mohamed Salah's Liverpool contract comments, branding them "selfish".

title: Live Ravens-Chargers updates: Harbaugh brothers clash on Monday Night Football
description: Jim's Chargers and John's Ravens are in the thick of the AFC playoff race, so tonight's matchup has more at stake than family bragging rights.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Longtime Utah football coach Kyle Whittingham unsure if he'll return for 21st season
description: Whittingham is college football's second-longest tenured head coach. He'll decide about his future at Utah after this season is over.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Bethell to bat at three on England Test debut
description: Jacob Bethell will bat at number three on his Test debut in England's series opener against New Zealand in Christchurch on Thursday.

title: Root 'a rung below' Smith and Kohli - Lehmann
description: England batter Joe Root needs to score a century in Australia to be considered an all-time great, says Darren Lehmann.
